						               													<description>Sail Ho! Campaign &amp;amp; Other Rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These Rules are a large expansion to the Basic Rules for Sail Ho!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These Rules are intended to allow players of the Sail Ho! Game to experience the organisation and running of a campaign set in the wider world of Napoleonic naval warfare. Many of these rules can be added to the Basic Rules without having to run a campaign, however.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Linked scenarios and challenges include Convoy duty, Harbour Raids, fire ships (left out of the basic rules; oops), Privateer actions, Blockade duty and the gathering of world-wide Trade to build national resources.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Commanders are introduced, each with their own special abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included in this package are more useful Game Counters, a Roster Sheet for organising your far-flung Fleets, and sample Fleets for other Nations; Russian, Swedish, Danish, Dutch, Portuguese, Spanish, Austrian, Naples and of course Pirates, and the various Merchantmen. Oh and a Blank sheet for adding your own.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
